~ back_inside_church
Aiden: The only way to find out what's going on is to go inside. I'll try to be quiet.
Door: [i]sqeeeeeak[/i]
Aiden: Hmmph. I don't remember it doing that when Father Matthew opened it.
Footsteps: [i]slumph[/i]
Footsteps: [i]slumph[/i]
Footsteps: [i]slumph[/i]
Aiden: My feet can't possibly be this loud all the time!
[i]::near door to Father's office, voices grow louder::[/i]
Father Matthew: --I assure you, Inquisitor, there is nothing for the Church to be concerned about here. The people are devout. I've been pastor at this church for more than two decades, and never have I seen people more godly than these.
Inquisitor: I am not here for your assurances, Father. I am here as the Eyes of God, and I will see for myself the way of things.
Inquisitor: There have been reports of the most terrible heresies, stamped from the Church proper centuries ago.
Inquisitor: My presence here is a blessing. If the reports are unfounded, you have nothing to fear for these folk... or for yourself. If, however, they are, then the swiftest action of the Church will set things right.
Father Matthew: I have neither hope, no fear, Inquisitor. I have only faith.
Inquisitor: That is all that is asked of any if us, Father.
Inquisitor: Even if your faith is strong, Father, it seems your punctuality is not. It is past noon. Are these people of yours so godly they do not need a reminder of their noon prayers?
Sister Beatrice: Forgive me, Inquisitor. That is my responsibility. I let your unexpected visit distract me from it.
Inquisitor: The offense is not against me, Sister, but against the Lord. Therefore forgiveness is not mine to give outside of Confession.
Inquisitor: But I suspect I will be hearing confessions while I am here.
A footstep comes closer to the door!
- Flee through the front door.
	Aiden: Whew! I... don't know what I just got away from but I feel like it's something. Oh, and they're about to ring the bell! Father Matthew gave me a break and I wasted it!
	=> aiden_travel_choice

- Stand your ground.

	Inquisitor: What is this... person?
	Father Matthew: Aiden! What brings you here? Oh, forgive me, Inquisitor, this is Aiden, one of our congregation. They were here earleir discussing... matters of... faith.
	Aiden: ?
	Inquisitor: ::peering at Aiden:: I did not say "who" Father, I said "what". I cannot tell if this is a man or woman I am looking at.
	Inquisitor: ::to Aiden:: What are you, then?
	- Answer Boldly.
		Aiden: I'm neither.
		Inquisitor: ::laughs::
		Inquisitor: Father, a [i]cow[/i] seems to have wandered into your church!
		Inquisitor: Or is it a [i]dog[/i]?
		Father Matthew: Inquisitor, please forgive Aiden... th-- he's never known when joking is inappropriate.
		Inquisitor: You would do well to remind this [i]godly[/i] flock of yours that God does not [i]joke[/i].
		Inquisitor: And when we joke, he laughs [i]at[/i] us, not [i]with[/i] us.
		Inquisitor: ::pushes past Aiden, exits the front door::
		- Aiden: [i]"He"[/i]??
		- Aiden: What was [i]that[/i] about?
		- Aiden: [i]::say nothing::[/i]
